<div1 type="summary">
<p>Sending a duplicate of his letter to President Jackson</p>
</div1>

<div1 type="body">

<p><location_mentioned>Columbia </location_mentioned><date_mentioned n="07-05-1836">5th July 1836</date_mentioned></p>

<p><person_mentioned>Col. Stephen F. Austin</person_mentioned>,</p>

<p>Regarded Sir,</p>

<p>In answer to your favor of today, I annex a duplicate of the letter to
<person_mentioned>Gen. Jackson</person_mentioned>, judging it to be better to do So, than to Send you a certified
copy; because the former may Serve in case the original Should be lost.</p>

<p><person_mentioned>A. L. de STA Ann</person_mentioned></p>

<p>A true translation. <location_mentioned>Velasco </location_mentioned><date_mentioned n="07-08-1836">8th July 1836</date_mentioned>.</p>

<p><person_mentioned>Edward Gritten</person_mentioned> [Rubric]</p>


</div1>
